==English==

===Phrase===
'''[[thank you]] [[very]] [[much]]'''

# Said to express greater gratitude than would be conveyed by [[thank you]].
# Obviously ''(principally UK; implying offence that anyone could have doubted the statement)
#* '''1997''', [[w:J. K. Rowling|J. K. Rowling]], ''[[w:Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone|Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone]]'' - Mr. and Mrs. Dursley, of number four, Privet Drive, were proud to say that they were perfectly normal, '''thank you very much'''.

====Synonyms====
* [[thanks a bunch]]
* [[thanks a lot]]
* [[thanks a million]]
* [[thanks very much]]
* [[thank you so much]]
* [[thank you so very much]]

